Former Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng. JOHANNESBURG - Former Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng has apologised for his comments regarding the Israel, Palestine conflict. This comes after an order by the Judicial Conduct Appeals Committee. The Committee last month ruled that Mogoeng breached the Judicial Code of Conduct by involving himself in matters that caused political controversy. READ: Mogoeng Mogoeng ordered to apologise for Israel comments He had until midnight to retract his statement. Mogoeng had previously remained adamant that his comments didn't undermine South Africa's Constitution but in a statement issued earlier, he affirmed he's not above the law.